      "content": "i mean, \"overwhelmingly agree\" sounds pretty definitive. isn't it true that there's a big debate about whether nonviolence was actually effective or if it just delayed the inevitable and made the government feel like they could control the movement? like, wouldn't it be more accurate to say there were different schools of thought rather than saying one was the primary way it worked?",
